Define Cross-Validation Scheme and Training Parameters

define_cv.Rd

See trainControl for info on how the seed is being set.

define_cv(
  train_data,
  outcome_colname,
  hyperparams_list,
  kfold = 5,
  cv_times = 100,
  group = NULL,
  seed = NULL
)

Arguments

train_data

Dataframe for training model
outcome_colname

column name as a string of the outcome variable
hyperparams_list

named list of lists of hyperparameters
kfold

fold number for k-fold cross-validation (default: 5)
cv_times

Number of partitions to create
group

vector of groups to keep together when splitting the data into train and test sets, and for cross-validation; length matches the number of rows in the dataset (default: no groups)
seed

random seed (default: NA)

Value

Caret object for trainControl that controls cross-validation

Author

Begüm Topçuoğlu, topcuoglu.begum@gmail.com
